Description: django-kube-form
        ================
        
        Reusable Django app for display [kube forms](http://imperavi.com/kube/forms/ "kube forms")
        
        ## Installation
        Install with pip: `pip install kubeform`
        
        Add `'kubeform',` to INSTALLED_APPS
        
        ## Usage
        
        Simple column form:
        
        ```html
        {% load kube %}
        
        <h2>Form</h2>
        <form method="POST">
            {{ form|kubecolumn }}
            <p>
        		  <input type="submit" class="btn" value="Send">
        	  </p>
        </form>
        ```
        
        Simple inline form:
        
        ```html
        {% load kube %}
        
        <h2>Form</h2>
        <form method="POST">
            {{ form|kubeinline }}
           <input type="submit" class="btn" value="Send">
        </form>
        ```
        
        Width fields:
        ```html
        {% load kube %}
        
        <h2>Form</h2>
        <form method="POST">
          {{ form.title|kubewidth:"50" }}
          <input type="submit" class="btn" value="Send">
        </form>
        ```
        
